          <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1rem">Mean vs Median vs Mode</h2>
          <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem"><strong>Mean (average):</strong> Sum of all values divided by the count. Most commonly used but sensitive to outliers.</p>
          <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem"><strong>Median:</strong> The middle value when numbers are sorted. Better for skewed data (e.g. salaries where a few very high values distort the mean).</p>
          <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.8"><strong>Mode:</strong> The value that appears most frequently. Useful for categorical data and finding the most common value.</p>
